      <abstract audience="internal" id="aspace_4ef3588c99894337e8a5880a68ec208c">The George E. May
        Papers, 1930s, contain 44 chapters (some missing) of a carbon-copy typescript manuscript
        plus handwritten drafts and other notes on the history of Port Republic, Virginia. The
        manuscript is a draft of May's book <emph render="italic">Port Republic: The History of a
          Shenandoah Valley River Town</emph> that was published for the first time in 2002 - the
        200th anniversary of the founding of Port Republic.</abstract>
    </did>
